<span id="freeTextContainer7390672971867152848">Wonderful book! I didn&apos;t know whether to expect a boring account of lots of battles and dates, but I didn&apos;t find that to be the case. I found the first half of the book to be fascinating. It was full of interesting accounts of himself and other people. It&apos;s a great, engaging, first person narrative of important history and a great story.<br/><br/>It did later get to be too much battle-account for me.<br/><br/>What Mark Twain said of the book: &quot;I had been comparing the memoirs with Caesar&apos;s Commentaries... I was abl</span>
  <span id="freeText7390672971867152848" style="display:none">Wonderful book! I didn't know whether to expect a boring account of lots of battles and dates, but I didn't find that to be the case. I found the first half of the book to be fascinating. It was full of interesting accounts of himself and other people. It's a great, engaging, first person narrative of important history and a great story.<br /><br />It did later get to be too much battle-account for me.<br /><br />What Mark Twain said of the book: "I had been comparing the memoirs with Caesar's Commentaries... I was able to say in all sincerity, that the same high merits distinguished both books—clarity of statement, directness, simplicity, unpretentiousness, manifest truthfulness, fairness and justice toward friend and foe alike, soldierly candor and frankness, and soldierly avoidance of flowery speech."</span>
