<div id="review_1856692315" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1856692315" />
    <a title="Chris" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3744803-chris"><img alt="Chris" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1365336928p2/3744803.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1856692315?book_show_action=true">Feb 09, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chris" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chris" href="/user/show/3744803-chris">Chris</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3744803-chris?shelf=civil-war">civil-war</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3744803-chris?shelf=the-presidents">the-presidents</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1856692315" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2416683938387108004">Grant wrote his memoirs in 1885 as a means to generate income for his family after his death. In his retirement, he had run into bad luck and been swindled out of much of his savings, which prompted him to begin writing his autobiography. I enjoyed the first third of the book which covered his early childhood, his West Point experiences and the Mexican American War. This portion had a personal tone and some of the stories he told were amusing and charming. The rest of the book was spent on the C</span>
  <span id="freeText2416683938387108004" style="display:none">Grant wrote his memoirs in 1885 as a means to generate income for his family after his death. In his retirement, he had run into bad luck and been swindled out of much of his savings, which prompted him to begin writing his autobiography. I enjoyed the first third of the book which covered his early childhood, his West Point experiences and the Mexican American War. This portion had a personal tone and some of the stories he told were amusing and charming. The rest of the book was spent on the Civil War years. I felt that this portion tended to be more matter of fact and frequently sounded more like an after action report of various battles rather than a narrative. I was hoping it would include more of his own insight and reflections. I would recommend Ronald C. White's biography <i>American Ulysses</i> to get a richer portrait of Grant.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2416683938387108004" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


